# API Documentation Rules

When API specifications are changed, you MUST update the documentation in `apps/docs/docs`:

- If you modify API endpoints, request/response formats, or data models in `apps/web/src/app/api/**`, update the corresponding documentation in `apps/docs/docs/04-developer-guide/api-reference/`
- If you change x402 protocol implementation, update the API specification document at `apps/docs/docs/04-developer-guide/api-reference/01-api-specification.md`
- Keep the documentation synchronized with the actual implementation
- Include examples and type definitions when updating API documentation
